    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1962-03-21T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1962-03-21T04:00:00-05:00" n="120"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d120">
                <head>120. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in Vietnam</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d120fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 751K.5/3-2162. Secret; <gloss target="#t_niact1">Niact</gloss>; Limit
                        Distribution. Received in the Department of State at 6:07 a.m. on March 21.
                        Repeated to Bangkok for <persName corresp="#p_HWA2">Harriman</persName>;
                            <gloss target="#t_CINCPAC1">CINCPAC</gloss> for <gloss
                            target="#t_Polad1">Polad</gloss>, <persName corresp="#p_NFEJ1"
                            >Nolting</persName>, and <persName corresp="#p_HGPD1"
                        >Harkins</persName>; and Clark Air Force Base. <persName corresp="#p_NFEJ1"
                            >Nolting</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_HGPD1">Harkins</persName>
                        were in Honolulu for the March Secretary of Defenseʼs Conference. The
                        message also requested that the Department of State pass it to the
                        Department of Defense.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Saigon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1962-03-21T17:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 21, 1962—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1200. COM <gloss target="#t_USMACV1">USMACV</gloss> 210531Z.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d120fn2">Not found.</note> Reference message reports joint US-<gloss
                        target="#t_GVN1">GVN</gloss> radar sightings unidentified aircraft in
                    numbers Pleiku area night of 19-20 March.</p>
                <p>Similar reports for night 20-21 March being checked. If confirmed, and evidence
                    strong for night 19-20 March, these sightings almost certainly involve aircraft
                    dropping supplies and/or reinforce meets <pb facs="0275" n="255" xml:id="pg_255"
                    /> to <gloss target="#t_VC1">VC</gloss>. Defense Minister <persName
                        corresp="#p_NDT2">Thuan</persName> telephoned me this morning indicating
                    grave concern and stressing need to take “precautionary measures”. <persName
                        corresp="#p_NDT2">Thuan</persName> subsequently relayed to General Weede
                    request from <persName corresp="#p_NDD2">Diem</persName> that US interceptors be
                    introduced <gloss target="#t_SVN1">SVN</gloss>.</p>
                <p>I strongly recommend that aircraft with night-fighter capability be dispatched
                    Saigon immediately with mission of confirming any future radar contacts and
                    shooting down any unfriendly aircraft detected over <gloss target="#t_SVN1"
                        >SVN</gloss>. This seems to me correct response from US standpoint to
                    Communist effort reinforce <gloss target="#t_VC1">VC</gloss> by air. It is
                    minimum response expected by <gloss target="#t_GVN1">GVN</gloss>.</p>
                <p>If aircraft are sent, I recommend they remain at least through present full moon
                    period and that they be represented publicly as “in transit”.</p>
                <p>General Weede is commenting separately to General <persName corresp="#p_HGPD1"
                        >Harkins</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_TWC2">
                            <hi rend="strong">Trueheart</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
